        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-09 17:35:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Looks good to me, approved\n\nPatch is fine, though one comment about the configure check - it should really be checking for the presence of the new feature (i.e. set_nlink() instead if the absence of the old feature (direct i_nlink access). This makes the test more clear as to what is the desired feature, and in cases where the feature is backported to older kernels (e.g. RHEL6) it will be used in preference to the old method and it would be more obvious if the compat code could be removed earlier.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
